The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India begin with a win 

New Delhi: India started their Sudirman Cup with a 4-1 defeat of Finland in Glasgow on Monday. 

In the mixed doubles, V. Diju and Aparna Balan set the tone with a 21-15, 21-9 win over Tuomas Nuorteva and Maria Vaisanen. Saina Nehwal then made it 2-0 after getting the better of Anu Nieminen 21-13, 21-13. 

Anup Sridhar lost to Ville Lang 11-21, 21-15, 16-21, but Thomas Sanave and Rupesh Kumar won the mens doubles with a 21-7, 21-15 win over Mikko Vikman and Nuorteva. Saina and Aparna made it 4-1 with a 21-11, 21-17 win over Elina and Maria Vaisanen. (PTI) 




